## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to design cross-region, multi-master transactional paths with real-time analytics, while honoring security and compliance constraints.

## Key Concepts
- DynamoDB Global Tables for low-latency multi-region writes
- CDC pipeline (Streams → Lambda → DMS/Debezium) to Aurora
- Conflict resolution and data governance for cross-region writes
- PCI-DSS residency and EU-centric encryption/backups

## Code Example
```javascript
// Lambda sample: process DynamoDB stream and push to Aurora via CDC
exports.handler = async (event) => {
  for (const rec of event.Records) {
    if (rec.eventName === 'INSERT' || rec.eventName === 'MODIFY') {
      const item = AWS.DynamoDB.Converter.unmarshall(rec.dynamodb.NewImage);
      await upsertAurora(item);
    }
  }
};
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you handle a write-conflict when two regions update the same item simultaneously?
- What monitoring and alerting would you implement to guarantee RPO and RTO targets under failover conditions?

## Why This Is Asked
The question probes practical enforcement of data residency DevOps patterns while maintaining low-latency reads and robust DR in a two-region setup. It tests architectural judgment on cross-region replication, routing, and tenant isolation.

## Key Concepts
- Aurora PostgreSQL Global Database with a single writer region and cross-region replicas
- Per-tenant data residency policies and region-aware schema partitioning
- Read routing to nearest replica to minimize latency
- RPO/RTO targets and PITR backups in multi-region setups

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudo routing logic for tenant requests
function routeRequest(tenantId, operation){
  const region = residencyMap[tenantId];
  if(operation === 'WRITE' && currentRegion !== region){
    throw new Error('Tenant not writable in this region');
  }
  // route to appropriate endpoint based on operation
  return regionEndpoints[region][operation];
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you handle a tenant migrating regions without data loss or RPO impact?
- How would you validate RPO/RTO during a simulated regional outage and during maintenance windows?

