## Why This Is Asked
Tests practical use of IAM DB authentication, RDS Proxy, and fine-grained access controls across accounts, plus a concrete testing plan.

## Key Concepts
- IAM database authentication with Aurora PostgreSQL
- RDS Proxy for serverless/large-concurrency access
- Fine-grained grants and per-service DB users
- Cross-account role mappings and network isolation
- Validation: latency, authorization, and failover tests

## Code Example
```sql
CREATE USER sales_read LOGIN;
GRANT USAGE ON SCHEMA sales TO sales_read;
GRANT SELECT ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA sales TO sales_read;

CREATE USER orders_rw LOGIN;
GRANT INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA orders TO orders_rw;
GRANT SELECT ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA orders TO orders_rw;
ALTER DEFAULT PRIVILEGES IN SCHEMA orders GRANT INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE ON TABLES TO orders_rw;
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you verify IAM role to DB user mapping using Lambda? 
- What monitoring would you set to detect privilege drift or misconfiguration?
